  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Multisectoral response to the conflict victims in Rwampara health zone,Irumu Territory in Ituri Province</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project aims to support the most vulnerable people in Ituri province who largely have settled unsheltered in public places, who are in need of non-food items (NFI) and emergency shelter. This includes those with special needs (older people, pregnant and lactating women, unaccompanied children, those with disabilities and chronic diseases) who are unsheltered. An unconditional cash intervention is appropriate in the affected area to cover the needs for food (for 15 days), NFIs, shelter, hygiene items and health especially for the disabled persons living with chronic diseases. The local market in the area remains accessible and has availability of items. The multipurpose cash grants will enable the targeted people to cater to their shelters to purchase essential household items, food stocks, seeds and can meet other needs of the household like health and education. T</narrative>
  </description>
